premise_source_doc_sentence: While Rosendale cement was extremely popular for the foundation of buildings  (  e.g. Statue of Liberty , Capitol Building , Brooklyn Bridge  )  and lining of water pipes , its long curing time of at least one month made it unpopular after World War I in the construction of highways and bridges , and many states and construction firms turned to Portland cement .
Cement is made from rocks containing lime , silica , and alumina ; Lehigh County limestone `` cement rock '' contains all three ingredients .
The cement was made from natural nodules of chalk and clay  (  `` septaria ''  )  from the Isle of Sheppey .
By 1900 the Lehigh Valley made 72 % of Portland cement produced in this country .
On the north side of Front St. was a large hill that made a great toboggan hill for the village kids to use in the winter .
